## Dependency Types

```bash
bd dep add <child> <parent>                         # child is blocked by parent (default)
bd dep add <finding> <source> --type discovered-from  # finding surfaced during source
bd dep add <dup> <original> --type duplicates         # dup is a duplicate of original
bd dep add <new> <old> --type supersedes              # new replaces old approach
```

---

## justfile targets

Add these to every project justfile:

```justfile
# Show unblocked tasks — run before any session
tasks:
    @bd ready --json | jq -r '.[] | "\(.id)\t\(.priority)\t\(.title)"'

# Create a task (usage: just task "Title" [priority 0-3])
task title priority="1":
    bd create "{{title}}" -p {{priority}}

# Claim a task
claim id:
    bd update {{id}} --claim

# Mark done and show what's next
done id:
    bd update {{id}} --status done
    @echo "Next unblocked tasks:"
    @bd ready --json | jq -r '.[0:3] | .[] | "\(.id) \(.title)"'
```

---

## Summary

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| `bd ready` before every session | Prevents working on blocked or deprioritized items |
| `--json` for programmatic output | Plain-text format is unstable; JSON is a contract |
| Agent recommendation in every task | Next agent knows who to assign without reading the whole task |
| Claim coordination + 10-min rule | Prevents two agents racing on the same task |
| `discovered-from` links | Full audit trail from any task back to the work that surfaced it |
| All tasks in `bd` | One system = no sync overhead, no duplication, no lost context |
| Planning docs in `history/` | Keeps repo root clean; docs are findable but not clutter |
| No markdown TODO lists | They immediately go stale and duplicate `bd` state |
| `bd sync` before `git push` | Task graph and code stay in lockstep across agents/machines |
| Land the plane before stopping | Nothing stranded locally; next agent has full context |
